@mloning I've got a coming PR that will handle the switch to the pydata theme, tweak some docstrings (e.g. if a docstring section was Return but should have been Returns, etc). 

Like we talked about I also think we should add a button above to update the `conf.py` to use `numpydoc` extension (currently it is not included, but `napoleon` is included even though our options later in the file are for `numpydoc`). My forthcoming PR will handle that as well. 

It also updates the templates for documenting classes (shows methods as mentioned above and also generates auto-summary table of methods). 


I'm just trying to sort through an issue where tweaks I make to the docstrings help to make docs render better and get rid of some warnings/errors when I run `make html` allow the docs to render like I expect but aren't making the underlying warning going away. For example, we have cases where we've left the 's' of the end of a docstring section (e.g. Return not Returns, Example not Examples). I've correct and docstrings are rendering but I'm still getting a warning that the class contains unknown section `Example` or `Return`. Something must be caching or something. 

@astrojuanlu any ideas on the caching thing and my inability to get rid of a warning that is no longer true?
